BinaryChopper
=============

This program takes any file, cut it up into smaller pieces and then merges those
pieces back again into the original file at some later time. Usefull for sending
large email attatchments or transfering large files over multiple smaller
storage units.

Build with `make` from the top directory.

Examples:
To cut a file into 4 pieces, execute:
  ./prog --cut 4 --file example.file

To merge those files againg, simply execute (from within the directory of the
data<num>.bin files):
  ./prog --merge


Erik Liodden
